title.narrative: COMMUNITY HEALTH WORKERS

description.narrative: By 2015, all rural districts of Mozambique have community health workers trained and deployed to provide essential maternal, newborn and child health services., which contributes to Child Health, Health Systems Strengthening, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: HEALTH - Vulnerable children and their families have access to, and make use of, quality promotive, preventive and curative health, nutrition and HIV services.

description.narrative: With UNICEF support, the community health worker programme was scaled-up in terms of total number of CHWs deployed and breadth of the service package for women and child. In 2016 the programme shifted focus to address remaining barriers of unequal distribution and quality leveraging mHealth technology. | Status:Met | As-of Date:19/01/2017
